02/03/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The Macedonian government confirmed Monday (1 March) that a team of experts has identified the remains of Macedonian President Boris Trajkovski, who died in a plane crash in Bosnia and Herzegovina on 26 February.The remains, identified at the Zagreb Forensic Institute's DNA laboratory, will be transferred to Skopje with the highest honours on Wednesday.
Top-level delegations from around 20 countries, as well as from NATO and the EU, are expected to attend Trajkovski's funeral Friday.The Macedonian government has said it will disburse 4,100 euros in assistance to the families of the delegation members and the pilots killed in the crash.
Prime Minister Branko Crvenkovski, meanwhile, sent a letter to NATO Secretary General Jaap de Hoop Scheffer asking for the Alliance's co-operation in determining the cause of the accident.
(Utrinski Vesnik - 02/03/04;
HINA, MIA, Makfax, A1 TV, AFP - 01/03/04)
